definition.value: This is an AE which is a complication of pregnancy; the acronym stands for Hemolysis, Elevated Liver enzymes, and Low Platelet count.

This is an AE which is a state of adaptation or dysregulation of thyrotropic feedback control wherein the levels of T3 and/or T4 are abnormal, but the thyroid gland does not appear to be dysfunctional.
This is an AE which is a vascular occlusion in humans in the region of the ulna.

This is an AE which is a rare congenital brain malformation in which the part joining the two hemispheres of the cerebellum (the cerebellar vermis) does not fully form, and the fourth ventricle and space behind the cerebellum (the posterior fossa) are enlarged with cerebrospinal fluid.
This is an AE which is a reaction of the skin to a viral infection.
This is an AE which is an autosomal recessive kidney tubule disorder characterized by low blood levels of potassium and magnesium, decreased excretion of calcium in the urine, and elevated blood pH.
This is an AE which is a postulated disorder of vision or image-processing in the brain.
This is an AE which is a rare congenital medical condition in which blood vessels and/or lymph vessels fail to form properly.

This is an AE which is defined as acute coronary syndrome (symptoms such as chest pain relating to reduced blood flow to the heart) caused by an allergic reaction or a strong immune reaction to a drug or other substance.
This is an AE which represents the asymmetric variant of chronic inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy (CIDP).

This is an AE which is a condition in which compression of the common venous outflow tract of the left lower extremity may cause discomfort, swelling, pain or clots (deep venous thrombosis) in the iliofemoral veins.
This is an AE which is a type of dystonia and is actually a combination of two forms of dystonia, blepharospasm and oromandibular dystonia (OMD).

This is an AE which is a medical condition, typically starting in young children, in which high fever occurs periodically at intervals of about 3-5 weeks, frequently accompanied by aphthous-like ulcers, pharyngitis and/or cervical adenitis (cervical lymphadenopathy).
This is an AE which is a severe endocrine disease caused by a corticotroph pituitary tumor and associated with increased morbidity and mortality.
This is an AE which is a rare disorder of unknown cause that is characterized by abundant histiocytes in the lymph nodes or other locations throughout the body.

This is an AE which is a rare disorder characterized by severe and unilateral headaches with orbital pain, along with weakness and paralysis (ophthalmoplegia) of certain eye muscles (extraocular palsies).
This is an AE which is a multisystem disease of presumed autoimmune cause that affects pigmented tissues, which have melanin.
This is an AE which is a chromosomal deletion syndrome resulting from a partial deletion on the short arm of chromosome 4 (del(4p16.3)).

This is an AE which is a rare genetic malformation syndrome characterized by the partial or complete absence of a key structure in the brain called the corpus callosum, the presence of retinal abnormalities, and seizures in the form of infantile spasms.
This is an AE which is a group of thirteen genetic connective-tissue disorders that are in the current classification, with a fourteenth type discovered in 2018.
This is an AE which is an autoimmune disease in which an individual's immune system attacks their own red blood cells and platelets, the syndrome can include immune neutropenia.
This is an AE which is a neuropsychological condition that causes a distortion of perception.
This is an AE which is a type of psychophysical visual disturbance in which a person with partial or severe blindness experiences visual hallucinations.
This is an AE which is an abnormal sensory perception during sleep in which a person experiences unreal noises that are loud and of short duration when falling asleep or waking up.
This is an AE which is a type of inflammatory disorder which affects multiple parts of the body.
This is an AE which is possible to argue that motor competence can be understood as the person s ability to carry out different motor skills and is become disorder.

This is an AE which is a condition in which a patient is aware but cannot move or communicate verbally due to complete paralysis of nearly all voluntary muscles in the body except for vertical eye movements and blinking.
This is an AE which is knee pain as a result of problems between the kneecap and the femur.
This is an AE which is a complex, fatiguing, long-term medical condition diagnosed by required primary symptoms and criteria, and often involves a broad range of symptoms.
This is an AE which is a condition in which people in a building suffer from symptoms of illness or become infected with chronic disease from the building in which they work or reside.
This is an AE which is generally a long-term disorder that causes a strong urge to move one's legs.
This is an AE which is a rare X-linked dominant genetic disorder that affects the skin, hair, teeth, nails and central nervous system.
This is an AE which is a neurological disorder causing a range of symptoms due to ischemia in the lateral part of the medulla oblongata in the brainstem.
This is an AE which is a hereditary autoinflammatory syndrome caused by mutations in the mevalonate kinase gene.
This is an AE which is a heterogeneous group of immune disorders.
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder characterized by mild-to-moderate intellectual disability.

This is an AE which is a clustering of at least three of the following five medical conditions: abdominal obesity, high blood pressure, high blood sugar, high serum triglycerides, and low serum high-density lipoprotein (HDL).
This is an AE which is a medical condition characterized by a snapping sensation felt when the hip is flexed and extended.
This is an AE which is a syndrome caused by a microdeletion on the long arm of chromosome 22.
This is an AE which is a congenital rare type of strabismus most commonly characterized by the inability of the eye to move outward.

This is an AE which is part of a group called Ras/MAPK pathway syndromes, is a rare autosomal dominant,multisystem disease caused by a mutation in the protein tyrosine phosphatase, non-receptor type 11 gene (PTPN11).
This is an AE which is altered organ function in an acutely ill patient requiring medical intervention to achieve homeostasis.
This is an AE which is an informal label that physicians apply to patients with symptoms similar to those of asthma.
